This paper discusses the use of data-driven models for dialogue systems, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of machine learning algorithms and evaluation metrics, which are relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the potential use of external knowledge, which is relevant to cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
